MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: (apps|packages)/.+\.(ts|tsx)$
MATCH_CONTENT: ['"](SYSTEM|SOCIAL|INTERNAL|CARTRIDGE|ADMIN|FACT|PRESENCE|TICKER|REJECTION)\.[A-Z_]+['"]
ADVISORY: |
  (Skip if editing packages/shared-types/src/events.ts — the source of truth
  — or a test snapshot where the string form is intentionally asserted.)

  Raw event-namespace string literal detected in the proposed edit.
  Pecking Order convention forbids raw strings for event types — import
  constants from `packages/shared-types/src/events.ts` instead.

  Wrong:
    if (type === 'SOCIAL.SEND_MSG') { ... }
    sendParent({ type: 'INTERNAL.READY' });
    const allowed = ['SYSTEM.SYNC', 'SOCIAL.SEND_MSG'];

  Right:
    import { Events } from '@pecking-order/shared-types';
    if (type === Events.Social.SEND_MSG) { ... }
    sendParent({ type: Events.Internal.READY });
    const allowed = [Events.System.SYNC, Events.Social.SEND_MSG];

  Applies to XState machines, WS handlers, allowlists, and client code.
  Source of truth: packages/shared-types/src/events.ts (Events namespace).
